win32ComputerSystemTable.name: win32ComputerSystemTable
win32ComputerSystemTable.description: The Win32-ComputerSystem class represents a computer system operating in a Win32 environment.

win32ComputerSystemAutomaticResetBootOpt.name: win32ComputerSystemAutomaticResetBootOption
win32ComputerSystemAutomaticResetBootOpt.description:
The AutomaticResetBootOption property determines whether the automatic reset boot option is enabled.

Values: TRUE or FALSE. If TRUE, the automatic reset boot option is enabled.

win32ComputerSystemAutomaticResetCapabil.name: win32ComputerSystemAutomaticResetCapability
win32ComputerSystemAutomaticResetCapabil.description:
The AutomaticResetCapability property determines whether the automatic reset is enabled.

Values: TRUE or FALSE. If TRUE, the automatic reset is enabled.

win32ComputerSystemBootROMSupported.name: win32ComputerSystemBootROMSupported
win32ComputerSystemBootROMSupported.description:
The BootROMSupported property determines whether a boot ROM is supported.

Values: TRUE or FALSE. If TRUE, a boot ROM is supported.

win32ComputerSystemBootupState.name: win32ComputerSystemBootupState
win32ComputerSystemBootupState.description:
The BootupState property indicates the bootup state of the computer system.

Constraints: Must have a value.

win32ComputerSystemCurrentTimeZone.name: win32ComputerSystemCurrentTimeZone
win32ComputerSystemCurrentTimeZone.description: The CurrentTimeZone property indicates the number of minutes the unitary computer system is offset from Greenwich Mean Time (GMT). The number is either positive, negative, or zero.

win32ComputerSystemDomain.name: win32ComputerSystemDomain
win32ComputerSystemDomain.description: The Domain property indicates the domain name of the computer system.

win32ComputerSystemInfraredSupported.name: win32ComputerSystemInfraredSupported
win32ComputerSystemInfraredSupported.description:
The InfraredSupported property determines whether an infrared (IR) port exists on the computer system.

Values: TRUE or FALSE. If TRUE, an IR port exists.

win32ComputerSystemManufacturer.name: win32ComputerSystemManufacturer
win32ComputerSystemManufacturer.description:
The Manufacturer property indicates the name of the computer manufacturer.

Example: Seagate

win32ComputerSystemModel.name: win32ComputerSystemModel
win32ComputerSystemModel.description:
The Model property indicates the model name of the computer system.

Constraints: Must have a value

win32ComputerSystemNetworkServerModeEnab.name: win32ComputerSystemNetworkServerModeEnabled
win32ComputerSystemNetworkServerModeEnab.description:
The NetworkServerModeEnabled property determines whether Network Server Mode is enabled.

Values: TRUE or FALSE. If TRUE, Network Server Mode is enabled.

win32ComputerSystemSupportContactDescrip.name: win32ComputerSystemSupportContactDescription
win32ComputerSystemSupportContactDescrip.description: The SupportContactDescription property is an array that indicates the support contact information for the Win32 computer system.

win32ComputerSystemSystemStartupOptions.name: win32ComputerSystemSystemStartupOptions
win32ComputerSystemSystemStartupOptions.description:
The SystemStartupOptions property is an array that indicates the options for starting up the Win32 computer system.

Constraints: Must have a value

win32ComputerSystemSystemStartupSetting.name: win32ComputerSystemSystemStartupSetting
win32ComputerSystemSystemStartupSetting.description: The SystemStartupSetting property indicates the index into the default start profile. This value is 'calculated' so that it usually returns zero (0) because at write-time, the profile string is physically moved to the top of the list. (This is how Windows NT determines which value is the default.)

win32ComputerSystemSystemType.name: win32ComputerSystemSystemType
win32ComputerSystemSystemType.description:
The SystemType property indicates the type of system running on the Win32 computer.

Constraints: Must have a value

win32ComputerSystemUserName.name: win32ComputerSystemUserName
win32ComputerSystemUserName.description:
The UserName property indicates the name of the currently-logged-on user.

Constraints: Must have a value

Example: John Smith

win32ComputerSystemStatus.name: win32ComputerSystemStatus
win32ComputerSystemStatus.description: The Status property is a string indicating the current status of the object. Various operational and non-operational statuses can be defined. Operational statuses are OK, Degraded and Pred Fail. Pred Fail indicates that an element may be functioning properly but predicting a failure in the near future. An example is a SMART-enabled hard drive. Non-operational statuses can also be specified. These are Error, Starting, Stopping and Service. The latter, Service, could apply during mirror-resilvering of a disk, reload of a user permissions list, or other administrative work. Not all such work is on-line, yet the managed element is neither OK nor in one of the other states.

win32TapeDriveTable.name: win32TapeDriveTable
win32TapeDriveTable.description: The Win32-TapeDrive class represents a tape drive on a Win32 system.

win32TapeDriveCompression.name: win32TapeDriveCompression
win32TapeDriveCompression.description: The Compression property indicates the compression level for the tape drive.

win32TapeDriveMediaType.name: win32TapeDriveMediaType
win32TapeDriveMediaType.description: MediaType is the type of media used or accessed by this device.

win32DiskDriveTable.name: win32DiskDriveTable
win32DiskDriveTable.description:
The Win32-DiskDrive class represents a physical disk drive as seen by a Win32 operating system. Any interface to a Win32 physical drive is a descendent (or member) of this class.

Example: IDE Fixed Disk

win32DiskDriveBytesPerSector.name: win32DiskDriveBytesPerSector
win32DiskDriveBytesPerSector.description:
The BytesPerSector property indicates the number of bytes per sector for the physical disk drive.

Example: 512

win32DiskDriveInterfaceType.name: win32DiskDriveInterfaceType
win32DiskDriveInterfaceType.description:
The InterfaceType property indicates the interface type of physical disk drive.

Example: IDE or SCSI

win32DiskDriveTotalCylinders.name: win32DiskDriveTotalCylinders
win32DiskDriveTotalCylinders.description:
The TotalCylinders property indicates the total number of cylinders on the physical disk drive.

Example: 657

win32DiskDriveTotalHeads.name: win32DiskDriveTotalHeads
win32DiskDriveTotalHeads.description: The TotalHeads property indicates the total number of heads on the disk drive.

win32DiskDriveTotalSectors.name: win32DiskDriveTotalSectors
win32DiskDriveTotalSectors.description:
The TotalSectors property indicates the total number of sectors on the physical disk drive.

Example: 2649024

win32DiskDriveTotalTracks.name: win32DiskDriveTotalTracks
win32DiskDriveTotalTracks.description:
The TotalTracks property indicates the total number of tracks on the physical disk drive.

win32DiskDriveTracksPerCylinder.name: win32DiskDriveTracksPerCylinder
win32DiskDriveTracksPerCylinder.description:
The TrackPerCylinder property indicates the number of tracks per cylinder on the physical disk drive.

win32DiskDriveIndex.name: win32DiskDriveIndex
win32DiskDriveIndex.description:

win32DiskDriveManufacturer.name: win32DiskDriveManufacturer
win32DiskDriveManufacturer.description:
The Manufacturer property indicates the name of the disk drive manufacturer.

win32DiskDriveMediaLoaded.name: win32DiskDriveMediaLoaded
win32DiskDriveMediaLoaded.description:
The MediaLoaded property determines whether the media for a removable disk drive is loaded.

win32DiskDriveModel.name: win32DiskDriveModel
win32DiskDriveModel.description:
The Model property indicates the manufacturer's model number of the disk drive.

Example: ST32171W

win32DiskDriveSCSIBus.name: win32DiskDriveSCSIBus
win32DiskDriveSCSIBus.description:
The SCSIBus property indicates the SCSI bus number of the disk drive.

Example: 0

win32DiskDriveSCSILogicalUnit.name: win32DiskDriveSCSILogicalUnit
win32DiskDriveSCSILogicalUnit.description:
The SCSILogicalUnit property indicates the SCSI logical unit number (LUN) of the disk drive.

Example: 0

win32DiskDriveSCSIPort.name: win32DiskDriveSCSIPort
win32DiskDriveSCSIPort.description:
The SCSIPort property indicates the SCSI port number of the disk drive.

Example: 0

win32DiskDriveSCSITargetId.name: win32DiskDriveSCSITargetId
win32DiskDriveSCSITargetId.description:
The SCSITargetId property indicates the SCSI ID number of the disk drive.

Example: 0

win32DiskDriveSize.name: win32DiskDriveSize
win32DiskDriveSize.description: The Size property indicates the size (in bytes) of the disk drive.

win32CDROMDriveDrive.name: win32CDROMDriveDrive
win32CDROMDriveDrive.description:
The Drive property indicates the drive letter of the CD ROM drive.

Example: d:

win32CDROMDriveFileSystemFlags.name: win32CDROMDriveFileSystemFlags
win32CDROMDriveFileSystemFlags.description:
The FileSystemFlags property indicates the file system flags of the Win32 CD ROM drive.

Example: 0

win32CDROMDriveId.name: win32CDROMDriveId
win32CDROMDriveId.description:
The Id property indicates the manufacturer's identifying name of the Win32 CD ROM drive.

win32CDROMDriveManufacturer.name: win32CDROMDriveManufacturer
win32CDROMDriveManufacturer.description:
The Manufacturer property indicates the manufacturer of the Win32 CD ROM drive.

Example: PLEXTOR

win32CDROMDriveMaximumComponentLength.name: win32CDROMDriveMaximumComponentLength
win32CDROMDriveMaximumComponentLength.description:
The MaximumComponentLength property indicates the maximum component length of the Win32 CD ROM drive.

Example: 0

win32CDROMDriveMediaType.name: win32CDROMDriveMediaType
win32CDROMDriveMediaType.description: The MediaType property is the type of media used or accessed by this Device.

win32CDROMDriveRevisionLevel.name: win32CDROMDriveRevisionLevel
win32CDROMDriveRevisionLevel.description: The RevisionLevel property indicates the firmware revision level of the Win32 CD ROM drive.

win32CDROMDriveSCSITargetId.name: win32CDROMDriveSCSITargetId
win32CDROMDriveSCSITargetId.description:
The SCSITargetId property indicates the SCSI ID number of the Win32 CD ROM drive.

win32CDROMDriveVolumeName.name: win32CDROMDriveVolumeName
win32CDROMDriveVolumeName.description:
The VolumeName property indicates the volume name of the Win32 CD ROM drive.

win32CDROMDriveVolumeSerialNumber.name: win32CDROMDriveVolumeSerialNumber
win32CDROMDriveVolumeSerialNumber.description:
The VolumeSerialNumber property indicates the volume serial number of the Win32 CD ROM drive.

win32CDROMDriveTransferRate.name: win32CDROMDriveTransferRate
win32CDROMDriveTransferRate.description: The TransferRate property returns the CD drive's transfer rate in kilobytes per second (KBytes/sec). A NULL value indicates that the rate could not be determined.

win32CDROMDriveDriveIntegrity.name: win32CDROMDriveDriveIntegrity
win32CDROMDriveDriveIntegrity.description: The DriveIntegrity property indicates whether files can be accurately read from the CD device.

win32CDROMDriveMediaLoaded.name: win32CDROMDriveMediaLoaded
win32CDROMDriveMediaLoaded.description:
The MediaLoaded property indicates whether a CD ROM is loaded.

Values: TRUE or FALSE. If TRUE, the media is loaded.

win32PointingDeviceTable.description:
The Win32-PointingDevice class represents a device used to point to regions on the display of a Win32 system. Any device used to point to regions on the display on a Win32 system is a member of this class.

Example: A mouse, stylus, touch pad, or tablet

win32PointingDeviceHardwareType.description:
The HardwareType property indicates the hardware type of Win32 pointing device.

win32PointingDeviceInfFileName.name: win32PointingDeviceInfFileName
win32PointingDeviceInfFileName.description:
The InfFileName property indicates the name of the INF file for the Win32 pointing device.

win32PointingDeviceInfSection.name: win32PointingDeviceInfSection

win32LogicalDiskTable.name: win32LogicalDiskTable
win32LogicalDiskTable.description: The Win32-LogicalDisk class represents a logical disk on a Win32 system.

win32LogicalDiskCompressed.name: win32LogicalDiskCompressed
win32LogicalDiskCompressed.description: The Compressed property indicates whether the logical volume exists as a single compressed entity, such as a DoubleSpace volume. If file based compression is supported (such as on NTFS), this property will be FALSE.

win32LogicalDiskDriveType.name: win32LogicalDiskDriveType
win32LogicalDiskDriveType.description:
The DriveType property contains a numeric representation of the type of disk drive represented by this logical disk.

Example: A CDRom would return 5

win32LogicalDiskFileSystem.name: win32LogicalDiskFileSystem
win32LogicalDiskFileSystem.description:
The FileSystem property indicates the file system on the logical disk.

Example: NTFS

win32LogicalDiskMaximumComponentLength.name: win32LogicalDiskMaximumComponentLength
win32LogicalDiskMaximumComponentLength.description: The MaximumComponentLength property indicates the maximum component length of the logical drive.

win32LogicalDiskProviderName.name: win32LogicalDiskProviderName

win32LogicalDiskSupportsFileBasedCompres.name: win32LogicalDiskSupportsFileBasedCompression
win32LogicalDiskSupportsFileBasedCompres.description:
The SupportsFileBasedCompression property indicates whether the logical disk partition supports file based compression, such as is the case with NTFS. If this property is TRUE, the Compressed property will be FALSE, but not necessarily vice versa.

Values: TRUE or FALSE. If TRUE, the logical disk supports file based compression.

win32LogicalDiskVolumeName.name: win32LogicalDiskVolumeName
win32LogicalDiskVolumeName.description:
The VolumeName property indicates the volume name on the logical disk.

Constraints: Maximum 32 characters

win32LogicalDiskVolumeSerialNumber.name: win32LogicalDiskVolumeSerialNumber
win32LogicalDiskVolumeSerialNumber.description:
The VolumeSerialNumber property indicates the volume serial number of the logical disk.

Constraints: Maximum 11 characters

win32LogicalDiskMediaType.name: win32LogicalDiskMediaType
win32LogicalDiskMediaType.description:
The MediaType property indicates the type of media currently present in the logical drive. This value will be one of the the values of the MEDIA-TYPE enumeration defined in winioctl.h.

Note: The value may not be exact for removable drives if currently there is no media in the drive.

win32DiskPartitionBootPartition.name: win32DiskPartitionBootPartition
win32DiskPartitionBootPartition.description:
The BootPartition property determines whether the partition is bootable.

Values: TRUE or FALSE. If TRUE, the partition is bootable.

win32DiskPartitionDiskIndex.name: win32DiskPartitionDiskIndex
win32DiskPartitionDiskIndex.description:
The DiskIndex property indicates the disk index number of the partition.

Example: 0

win32DiskPartitionHiddenSectors.name: win32DiskPartitionHiddenSectors
win32DiskPartitionHiddenSectors.description:
The HiddenSectors property indicates the number of hidden sectors in the partition.

win32DiskPartitionIndex.name: win32DiskPartitionIndex
win32DiskPartitionIndex.description:
The Index property indicates the index number of the partition.

Example: 1

win32DiskPartitionRewritePartition.name: win32DiskPartitionRewritePartition
win32DiskPartitionRewritePartition.description:

win32DiskPartitionSize.name: win32DiskPartitionSize

win32DiskPartitionStartingOffset.name: win32DiskPartitionStartingOffset

win32BatteryExpectedBatteryLife.name: win32BatteryExpectedBatteryLife
win32BatteryExpectedBatteryLife.description: The ExpectedBatteryLife property indicates the time in minutes of the expected life of the fully charged battery.

win32BatteryBatteryRechargeTime.name: win32BatteryBatteryRechargeTime
win32BatteryBatteryRechargeTime.description: The BatteryRechargeTime property indicates the time for recharging the battery.

win32MotherboardDevicePrimaryBusType.name: win32MotherboardDevicePrimaryBusType
win32MotherboardDevicePrimaryBusType.description:

win32ProcessorVersion.description:
The Version property indicates the version of the processor.

win32ProcessorL2CacheSize.description: The L2CacheSize property indicates the size in kilobytes of the processor's L2 cache.

win32PrinterAttributes.name: win32PrinterAttributes
win32PrinterAttributes.description:
The Attributes property indicates the attributes of the Win32 printing device.

Example: 64

win32PrinterDriverName.name: win32PrinterDriverName
win32PrinterDriverName.description:
The DriverName property indicates the driver name of the Win32 printing device.

Example: Windows NT Fax Driver

win32PrinterLocation.name: win32PrinterLocation
win32PrinterLocation.description: The Location property indicates the location of the Win32 printing device.

win32PrinterPrinterPaperNames.name: win32PrinterPrinterPaperNames

Example: B5 (JIS)

win32PrinterPortName.name: win32PrinterPortName
win32PrinterPortName.description:
The PortName property indicates the port name of the Win32 printing device.

Example: Sportster 56000 Fax Internal

win32PrinterPrintJobDataType.name: win32PrinterPrintJobDataType
win32PrinterPrintJobDataType.description: The PrintJobDataType property indicates the data type of the print job pending on the Win32 printing device.

win32PrinterSeparatorFile.name: win32PrinterSeparatorFile
win32PrinterSeparatorFile.description: The SeparatorFile property indicates the file printed between print jobs.

win32PrinterServerName.name: win32PrinterServerName
win32PrinterServerName.description: The ServerName property indicates the name of the server hosting the Win32 printing device.

win32PrinterShareName.name: win32PrinterShareName
win32PrinterShareName.description:
The ShareName property indicates the share name of the Win32 printing device.

Example: \\\\PRINTSERVER1\\PRINTER2

win32PrinterStartTime.name: win32PrinterStartTime
win32PrinterStartTime.description: The StartTime property specifies the earliest time at which the printer will print a job if the printer has been limited to print only at certain times.

win32PrinterUntilTime.name: win32PrinterUntilTime
win32PrinterUntilTime.description: The UntilTime property specifies the latest time at which the printer will print a job if the printer has been limited to print only at certain times.

win32PrinterDefaultPriority.name: win32PrinterDefaultPriority
win32PrinterDefaultPriority.description: The DefaultPriority property specifies the default priority value assigned to each print job.

win32PrinterAveragePagesPerMinute.name: win32PrinterAveragePagesPerMinute
win32PrinterAveragePagesPerMinute.description: The AveragePagesPerMinute property specifies the average number of pages per minute that have been printed on the printer.

win32PrinterPrintProcessor.name: win32PrinterPrintProcessor
win32PrinterPrintProcessor.description: The PrintProcessor property specifies the name of the print processor used by the printer.

win32NetworkConnectionStatus.name: win32NetworkConnectionStatus
win32NetworkConnectionStatus.description: The Status property is a string indicating the current status of the object. Various operational and non-operational statuses can be defined. Operational statuses are OK, Degraded and Pred Fail. Pred Fail indicates that an element may be functioning properly but predicting a failure in the near future. An example is a SMART-enabled hard drive. Non-operational statuses can also be specified. These are Error, Starting, Stopping and Service. The latter, Service, could apply during mirror-resilvering of a disk, reload of a user permissions list, or other administrative work. Not all such work is on-line, yet the managed element is neither OK nor in one of the other states.

win32ScheduledJobTable.name: win32ScheduledJobTable
win32ScheduledJobTable.description: The Win32-ScheduledJob class represents a job scheduled using the NT schedule service. This class isonly instrumented on NT3.51 and upwards. Each job scheduled against the NT schedule service is stored persistently and is executed at the specified time and day of the week and/or month. If the machine is not active or if thescheduled service is not running at the specified job time the schedule service will run the specified job on thenext day at the specified time.Scheduled jobs are scheduled with respect to UTC time, i.e. with bias offset from GMT. This means that a job can bespecified using any time zone specification. The Win32-ScheduledJob class will return the local time with UTC offsetwhen enumerating object and convert to local time when creating new jobs. For example a job specified to run on a computer in Chicago at 10:30 pm Monday PST time will be scheduled to run locally at 12:30am Tuesday CET. It should be noted that a client must take into account whether daylight...

win32ScheduledJobCommand.name: win32ScheduledJobCommand
win32ScheduledJobCommand.description: Command represents the executable name and command line arguments that the schedule service will use to invoke the job.Example. 'defrag /q /f'

win32ScheduledJobStartTime.name: win32ScheduledJobStartTime
win32ScheduledJobStartTime.description: StartTime represents the UTC time to run the job. This is of the form YYYYMMDDHHMMSS.MMMMMM(+-)OOO, where YYYYMMDD must be replaced by ****** Example. ********123000.000000-420 which implies 12:30 pm PST with daylight savings time in effect

win32ScheduledJobRunRepeatedly.name: win32ScheduledJobRunRepeatedly
win32ScheduledJobRunRepeatedly.description: RunRepeatedly represents whether the scheduled job, once created, will continue to run repeatedlyafter the first invocation of the job. Specify TRUE to repeatedly run the job, FALSE to run the job once anda value null to indicate to run the job once

win32ScheduledJobInteractWithDesktop.name: win32ScheduledJobInteractWithDesktop

win32ScheduledJobDaysOfWeek.name: win32ScheduledJobDaysOfWeek
win32ScheduledJobDaysOfWeek.description: DaysOfWeek represents what days of the week the job will be run on. If a Job has value null for both DaysOfWeek and DaysOfMonth,then the Job will be run either today or tomorrow depending on the specified StartTime and the current local time i.e. if it is12:30am and the job was created at 12:31am then the job will be run the following day.The value is a bitmask representing the day of the week, Sunday is specified as bit 0 and Saturday as bit 6. Each day can beinclusively Or'd to form a 7 bit value indicating the days of the week to run the job.

win32ScheduledJobDaysOfMonth.name: win32ScheduledJobDaysOfMonth
win32ScheduledJobDaysOfMonth.description: DaysOfMonth represents what days of the month the job will be run on. If a Job has value null for both DaysOfWeek and DaysOfMonth,then the Job will be run either today or tomorrow depending on the specified StartTime and the current local time i.e. if it is12:30am and the job was created at 12:31am then the job will be run the following day.The value is a bitmask representing the day of the month, the first day of the month is specified as bit 0 and and the last day of the month is specified as bit 30. Each month can beinclusively Or'd to form a 31 bit value indicating the days of the week to run the job.If the current month does not contain all 31 days within a month, the job will not be run for that particular day of the month

win32ScheduledJobJobStatus.name: win32ScheduledJobJobStatus
win32ScheduledJobJobStatus.description: JobStatus represents whether a Job created to run Repeatedly has been invocated at least once and that the last attempt resultedin a failure condition. Note that the JobStatus value 'Success' does not indicate that the job has already been run.

The TempDirectory property indicates the directory location where temporary files are stored.

Example: C:\\TEMP

win32DesktopTable.name: win32DesktopTable
win32DesktopTable.description:
The Win32-Desktop class represents the desktop layout of a Win32 system.

Example: The number and position of shortcuts on a Windows 95 or Windows NT workstation desktop

win32DesktopBorderWidth.name: win32DesktopBorderWidth
win32DesktopBorderWidth.description:
The BorderWidth property indicates the width of the desktop border.

Example: 1

win32DesktopCursorBlinkRate.name: win32DesktopCursorBlinkRate
win32DesktopCursorBlinkRate.description:
The CursorBlinkRate property indicates the time (in milliseconds) between cursor blinks.

Example: 530

win32DesktopDragFullWindows.name: win32DesktopDragFullWindows
win32DesktopDragFullWindows.description:
The DragFullWindows property determines whether the full window is displayed while being dragged.

Values: TRUE or FALSE. If TRUE, the full window is displayed while being dragged.

win32DesktopGridGranularity.name: win32DesktopGridGranularity
win32DesktopGridGranularity.description:
The GridGranularity property indicates the density of the desktop grid.

Example: 0

win32DesktopIconSpacing.name: win32DesktopIconSpacing
win32DesktopIconSpacing.description:
The IconSpacing property indicates the spacing (in pixels) between icons.

Example: 75

win32DesktopIconTitleFaceName.name: win32DesktopIconTitleFaceName
win32DesktopIconTitleFaceName.description:
The IconTitleFaceName property indicates the name of the current desktop typeface (font).

Example: MS San Serif

win32DesktopIconTitleSize.name: win32DesktopIconTitleSize
win32DesktopIconTitleSize.description:
The IconTitleSize property indicates the title size of the icons.

Example: 9

win32DesktopIconTitleWrap.name: win32DesktopIconTitleWrap
win32DesktopIconTitleWrap.description:
The IconTitleWrap property determines whether the icon title text wraps to the next line.

Values: TRUE or FALSE. If TRUE, the title text wraps to the next line.

win32DesktopName.name: win32DesktopName
win32DesktopName.description:
The Name property indicates the name of the current profile.

Example: MainProf

win32DesktopPattern.name: win32DesktopPattern
win32DesktopPattern.description: The Pattern property indicates the desktop pattern.

win32DesktopScreenSaverActive.name: win32DesktopScreenSaverActive
win32DesktopScreenSaverActive.description:
The ScreenSaverActive property determines whether the screen saver is active.

Values: TRUE or FALSE. If TRUE, the screen saver is active.

win32DesktopScreenSaverExecutable.name: win32DesktopScreenSaverExecutable
win32DesktopScreenSaverExecutable.description:
The ScreenSaverExecutable property indicates name of the current screen saver executable file.

Example: LOGON.SCR

win32DesktopScreenSaverSecure.name: win32DesktopScreenSaverSecure
win32DesktopScreenSaverSecure.description:
The ScreenSaverSecure property determines whether the screen saver is password enabled.

Values: TRUE or FALSE. If TRUE, the screen saver is password enabled.

win32DesktopScreenSaverTimeout.name: win32DesktopScreenSaverTimeout
win32DesktopScreenSaverTimeout.description: The ScreenSaverTimeout property indicates the amount of time before the screen saver takes effect.

win32DesktopWallpaper.name: win32DesktopWallpaper
win32DesktopWallpaper.description:
The Wallpaper property indicates the name of the wallpaper design.

Example: WINNT.BMP

win32DesktopWallpaperTiled.name: win32DesktopWallpaperTiled
win32DesktopWallpaperTiled.description:
The WallpaperTiled property determines whether the wallpaper is tiled or centered.

Values: TRUE or FALSE. If TRUE, the wallpaper is tiled.

win32DesktopWallpaperStretched.name: win32DesktopWallpaperStretched
win32DesktopWallpaperStretched.description:
The WallpaperStretched property indicates whether the Stretch Wallpaper to Fit Screen option is set. This can only be true if the user has the Microsoft Plus package installed.

Values: TRUE and FALSE. If TRUE, the Stretch Wallpaper to Fit Screen option is set. If Plus is not installed, this value is set to FALSE.

win32DisplayConfigurationTable.name: win32DisplayConfigurationTable
win32DisplayConfigurationTable.description:
The Win32-DisplayConfiguration class represents the display information of a Win32 system

Examples: Video adapter manufacturer, chipset version, display resolution, and number of colors

win32DisplayConfigurationBitsPerPel.name: win32DisplayConfigurationBitsPerPel
win32DisplayConfigurationBitsPerPel.description:
The BitsPerPel property indicates the number of bits required to represent the current state of a pixel.

Example: 8

win32DisplayConfigurationDeviceName.name: win32DisplayConfigurationDeviceName
win32DisplayConfigurationDeviceName.description: The DeviceName property indicates the name of the Win32 display device.

win32DisplayConfigurationDisplayFlags.name: win32DisplayConfigurationDisplayFlags
win32DisplayConfigurationDisplayFlags.description: The DisplayFlags property indicates the display flags of the Win32 display.

win32DisplayConfigurationDisplayFrequenc.name: win32DisplayConfigurationDisplayFrequency
win32DisplayConfigurationDisplayFrequenc.description: The DisplayFrequency property indicates the display frequency of the Win32 display.

win32DisplayConfigurationDitherType.name: win32DisplayConfigurationDitherType
win32DisplayConfigurationDitherType.description: The DitherType property indicates the dither type of the Win32 display.

win32DisplayConfigurationDriverVersion.name: win32DisplayConfigurationDriverVersion
win32DisplayConfigurationDriverVersion.description: The DriverVersion property indicates the driver version of the Win32 display.

win32DisplayConfigurationSpecificationVe.name: win32DisplayConfigurationSpecificationVersion
win32DisplayConfigurationSpecificationVe.description: The SpecificationVersion property indicates the specification version of the Win32 display.

win32DisplayControllerConfigurationTable.name: win32DisplayControllerConfigurationTable
win32DisplayControllerConfigurationTable.description:
The Win32-DisplayControllerConfiguration class represents the video adapter configuration information of a Win32 system.

Example: Jumper settings, Plug and Play information

win32DisplayControllerConfigurationBitsP.name: win32DisplayControllerConfigurationBitsPerPixel
win32DisplayControllerConfigurationBitsP.description:
The BitsPerPixel property indicates the current number of bits per pixel.

Example: 8

win32DisplayControllerConfigurationColor.name: win32DisplayControllerConfigurationColorPlanes
win32DisplayControllerConfigurationColor.description:
The ColorPlanes property indicates the current number color panes in the display.

Example: 2

win32DisplayControllerConfigurationDevic.name: win32DisplayControllerConfigurationDeviceEntriesInAColorTable
win32DisplayControllerConfigurationDevic.description:
The DeviceEntriesInAColorTable property indicates the current number of device entries in a color table.

Example: 256

win32DisplayControllerConfigurationDevic.name: win32DisplayControllerConfigurationDeviceSpecificPens
win32DisplayControllerConfigurationDevic.description:
The DeviceSpecificPens property indicates the current number of device-specific pens where 0xffff means the device does not support pens.

Example: 3

win32DisplayControllerConfigurationHoriz.name: win32DisplayControllerConfigurationHorizontalResolution
win32DisplayControllerConfigurationHoriz.description:
The HorizontalResolution property indicates the current number of pixels in the horizontal direction (X axis) of the display.

Example: 1024

win32DisplayControllerConfigurationName.name: win32DisplayControllerConfigurationName
win32DisplayControllerConfigurationName.description:
The Name property indicates the name of the current resolution and color setting.

Example: 1024 x 768 with 256 colors

win32DisplayControllerConfigurationRefre.name: win32DisplayControllerConfigurationRefreshRate
win32DisplayControllerConfigurationRefre.description:
The RefreshRate property indicates the refresh rate (in Hertz) of the video adapter. 0 or 1 indicate a default rate is being used. A -1indicates that an optimal rate is being used.

Example: 72

win32DisplayControllerConfigurationReser.name: win32DisplayControllerConfigurationReservedSystemPaletteEntries
win32DisplayControllerConfigurationReser.description:
The ReservedSystemPaletteEntries property indicates the current number of reserved entries in a system palette.

Example: 24

win32DisplayControllerConfigurationSyste.name: win32DisplayControllerConfigurationSystemPaletteEntries
win32DisplayControllerConfigurationSyste.description:
The SystemPaletteEntries property indicates the current number of entries in a system palette.

Example: 256

win32DisplayControllerConfigurationVerti.name: win32DisplayControllerConfigurationVerticalResolution
win32DisplayControllerConfigurationVerti.description:
The VerticalResolution property indicates the current number of pixels in the vertical direction (Y axis) of the display.

Example: 768

win32DisplayControllerConfigurationVideo.name: win32DisplayControllerConfigurationVideoMode
win32DisplayControllerConfigurationVideo.description:
The VideoMode property indicates the current pixel resolution and color setting of the display.

Example: 1024 X 768 with 256 colors.

win32LogicalMemoryConfigurationTable.name: win32LogicalMemoryConfigurationTable
win32LogicalMemoryConfigurationTable.description: The Win32-LogicalMemoryConfiguration class represents the logical memory configuration on a Win32 system.

win32LogicalMemoryConfigurationAvailable.name: win32LogicalMemoryConfigurationAvailableVirtualMemory
win32LogicalMemoryConfigurationAvailable.description:
The AvailableVirtualMemory property indicates the size (in bytes) of the available virtual memory.

Example: 2052288

win32LogicalMemoryConfigurationName.name: win32LogicalMemoryConfigurationName
win32LogicalMemoryConfigurationName.description: The Name property indicates the name of the logical memory configuration.

win32LogicalMemoryConfigurationTotalPage.name: win32LogicalMemoryConfigurationTotalPageFileSpace
win32LogicalMemoryConfigurationTotalPage.description:
The TotalPageFileSpace property indicates the total size (in bytes) of the page file.

Example: 524160

win32LogicalMemoryConfigurationTotalPhys.name: win32LogicalMemoryConfigurationTotalPhysicalMemory
win32LogicalMemoryConfigurationTotalPhys.description:
The TotalPhysicalMemory property indicates the total size (in bytes) of the physical memory.

Example: 40464

win32LogicalMemoryConfigurationTotalVirt.name: win32LogicalMemoryConfigurationTotalVirtualMemory
win32LogicalMemoryConfigurationTotalVirt.description:
The TotalVirtualMemory property indicates the total size (in bytes) of the virtual memory.

Example: 2093056

win32NetworkLoginProfileTable.name: win32NetworkLoginProfileTable
win32NetworkLoginProfileTable.description: The Win32-NetworkLoginProfile class represents the network login information of a particular user on a Win32 system.

win32NetworkLoginProfileAccountExpires.name: win32NetworkLoginProfileAccountExpires
win32NetworkLoginProfileAccountExpires.description:
The AccountExpires property indicates the date and time the account of a particular user expires.

Example: 20521201000230.000000000

win32NetworkLoginProfileBadPasswordCount.name: win32NetworkLoginProfileBadPasswordCount
win32NetworkLoginProfileBadPasswordCount.description:
The BadPasswordCount property indicates the number of times the user enters a bad password when logging on to a Win32 system.

Example: 0

win32NetworkLoginProfileCodePage.name: win32NetworkLoginProfileCodePage
win32NetworkLoginProfileCodePage.description: The CodePage property indicates the code page of the Win32 network login profile.

win32NetworkLoginProfileComment.name: win32NetworkLoginProfileComment
win32NetworkLoginProfileComment.description: The Comment property indicates a comment.

win32NetworkLoginProfileCountryCode.name: win32NetworkLoginProfileCountryCode
win32NetworkLoginProfileCountryCode.description: The CountryCode property indicates the country of the user.

win32NetworkLoginProfileFlags.name: win32NetworkLoginProfileFlags
win32NetworkLoginProfileFlags.description: The Flags property indicates the flags used in the NetWorkLoginProfile.

win32NetworkLoginProfileFullName.name: win32NetworkLoginProfileFullName
win32NetworkLoginProfileFullName.description: The FullName property indicates the full name of the user belonging to the network login profile.

win32NetworkLoginProfileHomeDirectory.name: win32NetworkLoginProfileHomeDirectory
win32NetworkLoginProfileHomeDirectory.description:
The HomeDirectory property indicates the home directory of the user.

Example: \\HOMEDIR

win32NetworkLoginProfileHomeDirectoryDri.name: win32NetworkLoginProfileHomeDirectoryDrive
win32NetworkLoginProfileHomeDirectoryDri.description:
The HomeDirectoryDrive property indicates the drive of the user's home directory.

Example: C:

win32NetworkLoginProfileLastLogoff.name: win32NetworkLoginProfileLastLogoff
win32NetworkLoginProfileLastLogoff.description:
The LastLogoff property indicates the date and time the user last logged off the system.

Example: 19521201000230.000000000

win32NetworkLoginProfileLastLogon.name: win32NetworkLoginProfileLastLogon
win32NetworkLoginProfileLastLogon.description:
The LastLogon property indicates the date and time the user last logged on to the system.

Example: 19521201000230.000000000

win32NetworkLoginProfileLogonHours.name: win32NetworkLoginProfileLogonHours
win32NetworkLoginProfileLogonHours.description: The LogonHours property is a string that specifies the times during which the user can log on.

win32NetworkLoginProfileLogonServer.name: win32NetworkLoginProfileLogonServer
win32NetworkLoginProfileLogonServer.description:
The LogonServer property indicates the name of the server onto which the user has logged.

Example: OCEANIA

win32NetworkLoginProfileMaximumStorage.name: win32NetworkLoginProfileMaximumStorage
win32NetworkLoginProfileMaximumStorage.description:
The MaximumStorage property indicates the maximum storage space that can be allocated to this user.

Example: 10000000

win32NetworkLoginProfileName.name: win32NetworkLoginProfileName
win32NetworkLoginProfileName.description:
The Name property indicates the name of the user.

Example: Joe Bloggs

win32NetworkLoginProfileNumberOfLogons.name: win32NetworkLoginProfileNumberOfLogons
win32NetworkLoginProfileNumberOfLogons.description:
The NumberOfLogons property indicates the number of logons at any given time.

Example: 4

win32NetworkLoginProfileParameters.name: win32NetworkLoginProfileParameters
win32NetworkLoginProfileParameters.description: The Parameters property indicates the parameters used in the NetWorkLoginProfile.

win32NetworkLoginProfilePasswordAge.name: win32NetworkLoginProfilePasswordAge
win32NetworkLoginProfilePasswordAge.description:
The PasswordAge property indicates the length of time a password has been in effect.

Example: 00001201000230.000000000

win32NetworkLoginProfilePasswordExpires.name: win32NetworkLoginProfilePasswordExpires
win32NetworkLoginProfilePasswordExpires.description:
The PasswordExpires property indicates date and time the password expires.

Example: 19521201000230.000000000

win32NetworkLoginProfilePrimaryGroupId.name: win32NetworkLoginProfilePrimaryGroupId
win32NetworkLoginProfilePrimaryGroupId.description: The PrimaryGroupID property indicates the ID of the primary group in the NetworkLoginProfile.

win32NetworkLoginProfilePrivileges.name: win32NetworkLoginProfilePrivileges
win32NetworkLoginProfilePrivileges.description: The privileges property indicates user privileges allowed for the NetworkLoginProfile.

win32NetworkLoginProfileProfile.name: win32NetworkLoginProfileProfile
win32NetworkLoginProfileProfile.description:
The Profile property contains information about the user.

Example: Administrator

win32NetworkLoginProfileScriptPath.name: win32NetworkLoginProfileScriptPath
win32NetworkLoginProfileScriptPath.description:
The ScriptPath property indicates the path to the user's logon script.

Example: C:\\win\\profiles\\JoeBloggs

win32NetworkLoginProfileUnitsPerWeek.name: win32NetworkLoginProfileUnitsPerWeek
win32NetworkLoginProfileUnitsPerWeek.description: The UnitsPerWeek property indicates the units used each week in the NetworkLoginProfile.

win32NetworkLoginProfileUserComment.name: win32NetworkLoginProfileUserComment
win32NetworkLoginProfileUserComment.description: The UserComment property indicates comments by users.

win32NetworkLoginProfileUserId.name: win32NetworkLoginProfileUserId
win32NetworkLoginProfileUserId.description: The UserId property indicates the name or logon alias of the user.

win32NetworkLoginProfileUserType.name: win32NetworkLoginProfileUserType
win32NetworkLoginProfileUserType.description: The UserType property indicates types of users.

win32NetworkLoginProfileWorkstations.name: win32NetworkLoginProfileWorkstations
win32NetworkLoginProfileWorkstations.description: The Workstations property indicates the workstations used in the NetworkLoginProfile.

win32OSRecoveryConfigurationTable.name: win32OSRecoveryConfigurationTable
win32OSRecoveryConfigurationTable.description: The Win32-OSRecoveryConfiguration class represents the configuration information necessary to recover from an operating system failure, such as a boot failure or system crash.

win32OSRecoveryConfigurationAutoReboot.name: win32OSRecoveryConfigurationAutoReboot
win32OSRecoveryConfigurationAutoReboot.description:
The AutoReboot property determines whether the system will be rebooted automatically during a recovery operation.

Values: TRUE or FALSE. If TRUE, the system will be automatically rebooted.

win32OSRecoveryConfigurationDebugFilePat.name: win32OSRecoveryConfigurationDebugFilePath
win32OSRecoveryConfigurationDebugFilePat.description: The DebugFilePath property indicates the full path to the debug file.

win32OSRecoveryConfigurationName.name: win32OSRecoveryConfigurationName
win32OSRecoveryConfigurationName.description: The Name property indicates the name used in the OSRecoveryConfiguration.

win32OSRecoveryConfigurationOverwriteExi.name: win32OSRecoveryConfigurationOverwriteExistingDebugFile
win32OSRecoveryConfigurationOverwriteExi.description:
The OverwriteExistingDebugFile property determines whether to overwrite an existing debug file. This property is valid only if the WriteDebugInfo property is set to TRUE.

Values: TRUE or FALSE. If TRUE, the existing debug file will be overwritten.

win32OSRecoveryConfigurationSendAdminAle.name: win32OSRecoveryConfigurationSendAdminAlert
win32OSRecoveryConfigurationSendAdminAle.description:
The SendAdminAlert property determines whether an alert message will be sent to the system administrator in the event of an operating system failure.

Values: TRUE or FALSE. If TRUE, the system will send an alert to the system administrator.

win32OSRecoveryConfigurationWriteDebugIn.name: win32OSRecoveryConfigurationWriteDebugInfo
win32OSRecoveryConfigurationWriteDebugIn.description:
The WriteDebugInfo property determines whether debug information will be written to a file.

Values: TRUE or FALSE. If TRUE, debug info is written a file.

win32OSRecoveryConfigurationWriteToSyste.name: win32OSRecoveryConfigurationWriteToSystemLog
win32OSRecoveryConfigurationWriteToSyste.description:
The WriteToSystemLog property determines whether system failure information will be written to a system log file.

Values: TRUE or FALSE. If TRUE, system failure information will be written to a system log file.

win32PrinterConfigurationTable.name: win32PrinterConfigurationTable
win32PrinterConfigurationTable.description: The Win32-PrinterConfiguration class defines a printer configuration.

win32PrinterConfigurationBitsPerPel.name: win32PrinterConfigurationBitsPerPel
win32PrinterConfigurationBitsPerPel.description:
The BitsPerPel property indicates the number of bits per pixel for the Win32 printer.

Example: 16

win32PrinterConfigurationCollate.name: win32PrinterConfigurationCollate
win32PrinterConfigurationCollate.description:
The Collate property determines whether to collate the print job.

Values: TRUE or FALSE. If TRUE, the printer collates the print job.

win32PrinterConfigurationColor.name: win32PrinterConfigurationColor
win32PrinterConfigurationColor.description:
The Color property indicates the color in which print jobs are produced.

Example: 0x000

win32PrinterConfigurationCopies.name: win32PrinterConfigurationCopies
win32PrinterConfigurationCopies.description:
The Copies property indicates the number copies to be printed.

Example: 2

win32PrinterConfigurationDeviceName.name: win32PrinterConfigurationDeviceName
win32PrinterConfigurationDeviceName.description: The DeviceName property indicates the name of the print device.

win32PrinterConfigurationDisplayFlags.name: win32PrinterConfigurationDisplayFlags
win32PrinterConfigurationDisplayFlags.description: The DisplayFlags property indicates the display flags for the Win32 printer.

win32PrinterConfigurationDisplayFrequenc.name: win32PrinterConfigurationDisplayFrequency
win32PrinterConfigurationDisplayFrequenc.description: The DisplayFrequency property indicates the display frequency for the Win32 printer.

win32PrinterConfigurationDitherType.name: win32PrinterConfigurationDitherType
win32PrinterConfigurationDitherType.description: The DitherType property indicates the dither type for the Win32 printer.

win32PrinterConfigurationDriverVersion.name: win32PrinterConfigurationDriverVersion
win32PrinterConfigurationDriverVersion.description: The DriverVersion property indicates the version of the Win32 printer driver.

win32PrinterConfigurationDuplex.name: win32PrinterConfigurationDuplex
win32PrinterConfigurationDuplex.description:
The Duplex property determines whether the print media is printed on both sides.

Values: TRUE or FALSE. If TRUE, the print media is printed on both sides.

win32PrinterConfigurationFormName.name: win32PrinterConfigurationFormName
win32PrinterConfigurationFormName.description:
The FormName property indicates the name of the form used for the print job.

Example: Cheques

win32PrinterConfigurationMediaType.name: win32PrinterConfigurationMediaType
win32PrinterConfigurationMediaType.description:
The MediaType property indicates the media type.

Example: Paper

win32PrinterConfigurationName.name: win32PrinterConfigurationName
win32PrinterConfigurationName.description:
The Name property indicates the name of the current printer configuration.

Character Set: Alphanumeric

win32PrinterConfigurationOrientation.name: win32PrinterConfigurationOrientation
win32PrinterConfigurationOrientation.description:
The Orientation property indicates the orientation of the print job.

Example: Landscape or Portrait

win32PrinterConfigurationPaperLength.name: win32PrinterConfigurationPaperLength
win32PrinterConfigurationPaperLength.description:
The PaperLength property indicates the length of the paper.

Example: 11

win32PrinterConfigurationPaperSize.name: win32PrinterConfigurationPaperSize
win32PrinterConfigurationPaperSize.description:
The PaperSize property indicates the size of the paper.

Example: A4 or Letter

win32PrinterConfigurationPaperWidth.name: win32PrinterConfigurationPaperWidth
win32PrinterConfigurationPaperWidth.description:
The PaperWidth property indicates the width of the paper.

Example: 8.5

win32PrinterConfigurationPrintQuality.name: win32PrinterConfigurationPrintQuality
win32PrinterConfigurationPrintQuality.description:
The PrintQuality property indicates the quality of the print job.

Example: Draft

win32PrinterConfigurationScale.name: win32PrinterConfigurationScale
win32PrinterConfigurationScale.description: The Scale property indicates the scale of the print job.

win32PrinterConfigurationSpecificationVe.name: win32PrinterConfigurationSpecificationVersion
win32PrinterConfigurationSpecificationVe.description: The SpecificationVersion property indicates the version of the specification.

win32PrinterConfigurationXResolution.name: win32PrinterConfigurationXResolution
win32PrinterConfigurationXResolution.description: The XResolution property indicates the resolution along the X axis (width) of the print job.

win32PrinterConfigurationYResolution.name: win32PrinterConfigurationYResolution
win32PrinterConfigurationYResolution.description: The YResolution property indicates the resolution along the Y axis (height) of the print job.

win32ProgramGroupTable.name: win32ProgramGroupTable
win32ProgramGroupTable.description: The Win32-ProgramGroup class represents a program group in a Win32 system, such as Accessories or Startup.

win32ProgramGroupGroupName.name: win32ProgramGroupGroupName
win32ProgramGroupGroupName.description:
The GroupName property indicates the name of the Win32 program group.

Example: Accessories\\System Tools

win32ProgramGroupName.name: win32ProgramGroupName
win32ProgramGroupName.description:
The Name property indicates the user name followed by the group name.

Example: All Users:Accessories\\System Tools

win32ProgramGroupUserName.name: win32ProgramGroupUserName
win32ProgramGroupUserName.description:
The UserName property indicates the users who can access the Win32 program group.

Example: All Users

win32SerialPortConfigurationTable.name: win32SerialPortConfigurationTable
win32SerialPortConfigurationTable.description: The Win32-SerialPortConfiguration class represents a serial port configuration.

win32SerialPortConfigurationAbortReadWri.name: win32SerialPortConfigurationAbortReadWriteOnError
win32SerialPortConfigurationAbortReadWri.description:
The AbortReadWriteOnError property determines whether to abort a read or write operation when an error occurs.

Values: TRUE or FALSE. If TRUE, the operation is aborted.

win32SerialPortConfigurationBaudRate.name: win32SerialPortConfigurationBaudRate
win32SerialPortConfigurationBaudRate.description:
The BaudRate property indicates the baud rate for this serial port.

Example: 9600

win32SerialPortConfigurationBinaryModeEn.name: win32SerialPortConfigurationBinaryModeEnabled
win32SerialPortConfigurationBinaryModeEn.description:
The BinaryModeEnabled property determines whether binary mode is enabled for the serial port.

Values: TRUE or FALSE. If TRUE, binary mode is enabled.

win32SerialPortConfigurationBitsPerByte.name: win32SerialPortConfigurationBitsPerByte
win32SerialPortConfigurationBitsPerByte.description:
The BitsPerByte property indicates the number of bits per byte for the Win32 serial port.

Example: 8

win32SerialPortConfigurationCTSOutflowCo.name: win32SerialPortConfigurationCTSOutflowControl
win32SerialPortConfigurationCTSOutflowCo.description:
The CTSOutflowControl property determines whether data outflow control is enabled when there is a Clear To Send (CTS) condition.

Values: TRUE or FALSE. If TRUE, CTS outflow control is enabled.

win32SerialPortConfigurationDiscardNULLB.name: win32SerialPortConfigurationDiscardNULLBytes
win32SerialPortConfigurationDiscardNULLB.description:
The DiscardNULLBytes property determines whether to discard NULL bytes (characters).

Values: TRUE or FALSE. If TRUE, NULL bytes are discarded.

win32SerialPortConfigurationDSROutflowCo.name: win32SerialPortConfigurationDSROutflowControl
win32SerialPortConfigurationDSROutflowCo.description:
The DSROutflowControl property determines whether data outflow control is enabled when there is a Data Set Read (DSR) condition.

Values: TRUE or FALSE. If TRUE, DSR outflow control is enabled.

win32SerialPortConfigurationDSRSensitivi.name: win32SerialPortConfigurationDSRSensitivity
win32SerialPortConfigurationDSRSensitivi.description:
The DSRSensitivity property determines whether DSR sensitivity is enabled.

Values: TRUE or FALSE. If TRUE, DSR sensitivity is enabled.

win32SerialPortConfigurationDTRFlowContr.name: win32SerialPortConfigurationDTRFlowControlType
win32SerialPortConfigurationDTRFlowContr.description:
The DTRFlowControlType property indicates the type of data terminal ready (DTR) flow control.

Character Set: Alphanumeric

win32SerialPortConfigurationEOFCharacter.name: win32SerialPortConfigurationEOFCharacter
win32SerialPortConfigurationEOFCharacter.description:
The EOFCharacter property indicates the end of file (EOF) character.

Example: ^Z

win32SerialPortConfigurationErrorReplace.name: win32SerialPortConfigurationErrorReplaceCharacter
win32SerialPortConfigurationErrorReplace.description:
The ErrorReplaceCharacter property indicates the error replace character.

Example: ^C

win32SerialPortConfigurationErrorReplace.name: win32SerialPortConfigurationErrorReplacementEnabled
win32SerialPortConfigurationErrorReplace.description:
The ErrorReplacementEnabled property determines whether error replacement is enabled.

Values: TRUE or FALSE. If TRUE, error replacement is enabled.

win32SerialPortConfigurationEventCharact.name: win32SerialPortConfigurationEventCharacter
win32SerialPortConfigurationEventCharact.description:
The EventCharacter property indicates the event character.

Example: ^e

win32SerialPortConfigurationIsBusy.name: win32SerialPortConfigurationIsBusy
win32SerialPortConfigurationIsBusy.description:
The IsBusy property determines whether the serial port is busy.

Values: TRUE or FALSE. If TRUE, the serial port is busy.

win32SerialPortConfigurationName.name: win32SerialPortConfigurationName
win32SerialPortConfigurationName.description:
The Name property indicates the name of the Win32 serial port.

Example: COM1

win32SerialPortConfigurationParity.name: win32SerialPortConfigurationParity
win32SerialPortConfigurationParity.description:
The Parity property indicates the type of parity used.

Example: None, Even, or Odd

win32SerialPortConfigurationParityCheckE.name: win32SerialPortConfigurationParityCheckEnabled
win32SerialPortConfigurationParityCheckE.description:
The ParityCheckEnabled property determines whether parity checking is enabled.

Values: TRUE or FALSE. If TRUE, parity checking is enabled.

win32SerialPortConfigurationRTSFlowContr.name: win32SerialPortConfigurationRTSFlowControlType
win32SerialPortConfigurationRTSFlowContr.description:
The RTSFlowControlType property indicates the type of ready to send (RTS) flow control.

Character Set: Alphanumeric

win32SerialPortConfigurationStopBits.name: win32SerialPortConfigurationStopBits
win32SerialPortConfigurationStopBits.description:
The StopBits property indicates the number of stop bits for the Win32 serial port.

Example: 1

win32SerialPortConfigurationXOffCharacte.name: win32SerialPortConfigurationXOffCharacter
win32SerialPortConfigurationXOffCharacte.description: The XOffCharacter property indicates the XOff character for the Win32 serial port.

win32SerialPortConfigurationXOffXMitThre.name: win32SerialPortConfigurationXOffXMitThreshold
win32SerialPortConfigurationXOffXMitThre.description: The XOffXMitThreshold property indicates the XOff transmit threshold for the Win32 serial port.

win32SerialPortConfigurationXOnCharacter.name: win32SerialPortConfigurationXOnCharacter
win32SerialPortConfigurationXOnCharacter.description: The XOnCharacter property indicates the XOn character.

win32SerialPortConfigurationXOnXMitThres.name: win32SerialPortConfigurationXOnXMitThreshold
win32SerialPortConfigurationXOnXMitThres.description: The XOnXMitThreshold property indicates the XOn transmit threshold.

win32SerialPortConfigurationXOnXOffInFlo.name: win32SerialPortConfigurationXOnXOffInFlowControl
win32SerialPortConfigurationXOnXOffInFlo.description: The XOnXOffInFlowControl property indicates the amount of data inflow.

win32SerialPortConfigurationXOnXOffOutFl.name: win32SerialPortConfigurationXOnXOffOutFlowControl
win32SerialPortConfigurationXOnXOffOutFl.description: The XOnXOffOutFlowControl property indicates the amount of data outflow.

win32TimeZoneTable.name: win32TimeZoneTable
win32TimeZoneTable.description: The Win32-TimeZone class represents the time zone information for a Win32 system. For example, (GMT08:00) Pacific Time (US & Canada); Tijuana.

win32TimeZoneBias.name: win32TimeZoneBias
win32TimeZoneBias.description: The bias property indicates the bias of the time zone.

win32TimeZoneDaylightBias.name: win32TimeZoneDaylightBias
win32TimeZoneDaylightBias.description: The DaylightBias property indicates the bias during daylight saving time.

win32TimeZoneDaylightDay.name: win32TimeZoneDaylightDay
win32TimeZoneDaylightDay.description:
The DaylightDay property indicates the day during daylight saving time.

Example: 31

win32TimeZoneDaylightDayOfWeek.name: win32TimeZoneDaylightDayOfWeek
win32TimeZoneDaylightDayOfWeek.description:
The DaylightDayOfWeek property indicates the day of the week during daylight saving time.

Example: Monday

win32TimeZoneDaylightHour.name: win32TimeZoneDaylightHour
win32TimeZoneDaylightHour.description:
The DaylightHour property indicates the hour of the day during daylight saving time.

Example: 11

win32TimeZoneDaylightMillisecond.name: win32TimeZoneDaylightMillisecond
win32TimeZoneDaylightMillisecond.description: The DaylightMillisecond property indicates a millionth of a second during daylight saving time.

win32TimeZoneDaylightMinute.description:
The DaylightMinute property indicates a minute during daylight saving time.

Example: 59

win32TimeZoneDaylightMonth.name: win32TimeZoneDaylightMonth
win32TimeZoneDaylightMonth.description:
The DaylightMonth property indicates the month of the year during daylight saving time.

Example: 4

win32TimeZoneDaylightName.name: win32TimeZoneDaylightName
